+id: ui-app-experience-polish-001
+title: Polish the signed-in Sello app experience without touching landing or backend systems
+status: ready
+owner: Cursor/Grok
+reviewer: Codex
+risk: medium
+task_type: ui
+base_branch: develop
+working_branch: feature/app-experience-polish
+worktree_path: /Users/jheller/dev/resale-crosslister-app-experience
+created_at: 2026-07-10T18:00:00.000Z
+goal: Make the signed-in dashboard, inventory, listing, channels, and settings experience feel intentional, sleek, modern, coherent, responsive, and distinctly Sello while preserving all functionality and the current logo.
+context: The marketing landing page is owned by a separate active task, so this contract deliberately excludes landing files and globals.css. The signed-in app already uses a shared shell and design tokens; this task refines hierarchy, density, states, and interaction polish within app-owned components only.
+non_goals:
+  - No landing page, public marketing, pricing, privacy, contact, root layout, or global stylesheet changes.
+  - No API, database, auth, billing logic, marketplace behavior, comps/provider behavior, inventory-sync logic, feature flags, dependencies, CI, or deployment changes.
+  - No Sello logo, wordmark, or brand-mark replacement.
+  - No new product capability or simulated marketplace behavior.
+allowed_paths:
+  - .agent/**
+  - src/app/(app)/**
