+acceptance:
+  - The current Sello logo and wordmark remain unchanged and are used consistently in the signed-in shell.
+  - Dashboard, inventory list/grid and empty/loading/error states, listing detail/editor, channels, and settings share a clear visual hierarchy, consistent spacing, controls, cards, and feedback states.
+  - Existing routes, data loading, mutations, navigation, feature gates, publish/delist readiness, billing states, and inventory behavior remain functionally unchanged.
+  - Seller-facing copy uses listing terminology and never claims unsupported automation or marketplace success.
+  - The experience is usable at 1440px desktop, 1024px tablet, and 390px mobile without horizontal overflow, clipped actions, unreadable density, or inaccessible drawers/modals.
+  - Keyboard navigation, visible focus, semantic headings/landmarks, labels, contrast, touch targets, and reduced-motion behavior are reviewed and repaired within allowed paths.
+  - Motion is purposeful, respects prefers-reduced-motion, and does not block task completion or obscure state.
